  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients benefitting from a lung transplantation are subject to long-lasting and often severe
      post-operative pain. Self-hypnosis has been proven effective in the management of acute pain.

      The study hypothesis is that pre-operative training in self-hypnosis given to patients
      awaiting lung transplantation, will result in a reduction of post-operative pain one month
      after surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
